ion testifying to their achievement, and all student transcripts will reflect credit hours/certificates earned. UIC’s certificate programs may be offered in a variety of instructional formats—online, blended, or classroom.  Campus Certificates are listed below. Refer to the Degree Programs section for a list of IBHE-Approved Certificates.          Certificate Program  College/School  Program Code  Program Information     Advanced Practice Palliative Care Nursing  Nursing  20FS5068NDEU  http://www.nursing.uic.edu/academics-admissions/advanced-practice-palliative-care-nursing-certificate#about-the-program   Applied Startup Knowledge  Business Administration  20FL5482NDEG  https://ies.uic.edu/applied-startup-knowledge-ask-certificate-program   Assistive Technology  Applied Health Sciences  20FS5022NDEG  https://ahs.uic.edu/disability-human-development/admissions-and-programs/assistive-technology-certificate   Basic Community Public Health Practice (admission is suspended)  Public Health  20FY5108NDEU  http://publichealth.uic.edu/basic-community-public-health-practice   Bioinformatics  Engineering  20FQ5001NDEU  http://meng.uic.edu/program-info/certificates   Clinical Rehabilitation and Technology Research  Applied Health Sciences  20FS5509NDEG  https://ahs.uic.edu/physical-therapy/admissions-and-programs/certificate-in-clinical-rehabilitation-and-technology-research/   Clinical Research Methodsᵇ  Public Health  2PFS5189NDEU  Admission to the program is suspended. Please contact the college for more information.   Disability Ethics  Applied Health Sciences  20FS5558NDEG  https://ahs.uic.edu/disability-human-development/admissions-and-programs/disability-ethics-certificate   Disaster Management  Engineering  20FQ5557NDEU  http://meng.uic.edu/program-info/certificates   Educational Research Methodology  Education  2PFS5208NDEU  http://mesaonline.ec.uic.edu/programs/graduate-certificate-educational-research-methodology   e-Government[b]  Urban Planning and Public Affairs  